<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ANTILOCK BRAKES/TRACTION CONTROL: BENDIX - TROUBLESHOOTING - 9800 MODEL - TESTING FOR FALSE INDICATION
        CAUSED BY ABS WARNING LIGHT
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="0">
        <title>TESTING FOR FALSE INDICATION CAUSED BY ABS WARNING LIGHT</title>
        <table id="t0403517" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
            <title>Testing For False Indication Caused By ABS Warning Light</title>
            <tgroup cols="6" align="center" charoff="50" char="c">
                <colspec colname="1" colwidth="0.92in"/>
                <colspec colname="2" colwidth="0.92in"/>
                <colspec colname="3" colwidth="0.92in"/>
                <colspec colname="4" colwidth="0.92in"/>
                <colspec colname="5" colwidth="0.92in"/>
                <colspec colname="6" colwidth="0.92in"/>
                <spanspec namest="1" nameend="6" spanname="s1t6" align="center"/>
                <thead>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="6" spanname="s1t6">
                            <para>This test should be performed if: 1. The ABS Warning Light on the instrument panel
                                remains On, 2. There are no Red LEDs ON, 3. The Green VLT LED Is ON but not flashing.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </thead>
                <tbody valign="top">
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>STEP</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>KEY</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>ACTION</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>SPEC.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>YES / IN SPEC.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>NO / OUT OF SPEC.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>1.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Hold magnet on LED reset and note if all LEDs illuminate.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>All LEDs ON.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Replace the controller.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>2.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off/On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Disconnect connector (627) from controller. Install a jumper wire from pin E3 of
                                harness connector (627) to gnd. Move key to ON and note if ABS Warning Light turned OFF.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>ABS light OFF.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>Re-inspect connectors and replace controller if connections OK.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>3.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Remove ABS Warning Light relay from relay socket (443). Bench test relay by applying
                                +12V to pin 86, gnd. to pin 85, and measuring resistance from pin 30 to 87A.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>> 100K ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Replace defective relay.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>4.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Locate short to ground in circuit 94E between connectors (363) and (443) or short in
                                gauge cluster, then repair. Re-install relay and reconnect connector (627).
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
